    "notes": "Played 22h: a mix of slow stealth but rushed the game at the end.\nRating: Gold. The game has been \u2018perfect\u2019 for 90-95% of the time. I didn\u2019t \u2018need\u2019 or make any tweaks. It ran great out the box, but some more tweaking or work is needed for prime time.\n\n\nThe big problems:\n\nProblem 1. The mouse sensativity frequently was reduced. I think this happened once on EVERY mission. This stopped me playing anyfurther. I think this is game bug. It feels like the limited camera panning of a cut scene. I tried switching mice, I\u2019ve had luck pressing the \u201cEsc\u201d key for the menu. I\u2019ve also closed and restarted the game. I didn\u2019t nail down this issue sorry.\n\nProblem 2. I had serious graphics and texture issues with \u201cReturn to Dunwall Tower\u201d for example the entire floor would be transparent. Again I\u2019ve also closed and restarted the game which \u2018fixed\u2019 the issue. I didn\u2019t nail down this issue sorry.\n\nProblem 3. Consistant Performance. Most of the game, most of the time has been fantastic. I\u2019ve had 55-60 fps for 95% of my time and I didn\u2019t notice. But then I hit a few moments of 30-40 fps in \u201cReturn to Dunwall Tower\u201d which I did notice. My early play style was covert and exploratory, later I started to rush through; I feel the early levels where fine, and I can\u2019t fully comment on the others.\n",
